cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper presents a method for improving end-to-end control systems via data aggregation using uncertainty estimation. The paper focuses on applications in safety-critical domains such as autonomous driving. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a new algorithm for deep imitation learning. The paper also involves the use of Monte Carlo Dropout to estimate uncertainty in the control output, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on autonomous driving tasks suggests that it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques for simulated driving tasks, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's focus on safety-critical domains suggests that it could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
